{"title_page": "Jesper Bank", "text_new": "{{short description|Danish sailor and Olympic champion|bot=PearBOT 5}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2015}}\n{{MedalTableTop}}\n{{MedalSport | Men's [[Sailing (sport)|sailing]]}}\n{{MedalCountry | {{DEN}} }}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[Olympic Games]]}}\n{{MedalGold| [[1992 Summer Olympics|1992 Barcelona]] | [[Sailing at the 1992 Summer Olympics|Soling class]]}}\n{{MedalGold| [[2000 Summer Olympics|2000 Sydney]] | [[Sailing at the 2000 Summer Olympics|Soling class]]}}\n{{MedalBronze| [[1988 Summer Olympics|1988 Seoul]] | [[Sailing at the 1988 Summer Olympics|Soling class]]}}\n{{MedalBottom}}\n\n'''Jesper Bank''' (born 6 April 1957 in [[Fredericia]]) is a [[Denmark|Danish]] [[sailor]] and Olympic champion. \nHe received a bronze medal in the ''[[Soling|Soling Class]]'' at the [[1988 Summer Olympics]] in [[Seoul]].<ref name=db-ol1988-sailing>[https://web.archive.org/web/20061031065851/http://www.databaseolympics.com/games/gamessport.htm?g=22&sp=YAT 1988 Summer Olympics &ndash; Seoul, South Korea &ndash; Sailing] &ndash; ''databaseOlympics.com'' (Retrieved on 23 May 2008)</ref>\n\nHe won a gold medal at the [[1992 Summer Olympics]] in [[Barcelona]],<ref name=db-ol1992-sailing>[https://web.archive.org/web/20060218162535/http://databaseolympics.com/games/gamessport.htm?g=23&sp=YAT 1992 Summer Olympics &ndash; Barcelona, Spain &ndash; Sailing] &ndash; ''databaseOlympics.com'' (Retrieved on 23 May 2008)</ref> and again at the [[2000 Summer Olympics]] in [[Sydney]].<ref name=db-ol2000-sailing>[http://www.databaseolympics.com/games/gamessport.htm?g=25&sp=YAT 2000 Summer Olympics &ndash; Sydney, Australia &ndash; Sailing] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131016101855/http://www.databaseolympics.com/games/gamessport.htm?g=25&sp=YAT |date=16 October 2013 }} &ndash; ''databaseOlympics.com'' (Retrieved on 23 May 2008)</ref>\n\nThis makes Jesper Bank among the most winning regatta and match-race sailors seen.\nBetween 1978 (nationally) relatively 1987 (internationally) and 2000 achieved he to be:\n\n- Twice Olympic champion and additional one time bronze medallist. \n\n- 8 times World Champion and additional 5 times medallist.\n\n- 3 times European Champion and additional 3 times medallist.\n\n- Scandinavian Champion and additional two times bronze medallist.\n\n- 9 times national Danish Champion and additional a single Bronze medal.\n\nThe international and some national results though as skipper in 3-crew boat classes.\n\nHe sailed for [[Victory Challenge]] in the [[2003 Louis Vuitton Cup]] and [[United Internet Team Germany]] in the [[2007 Louis Vuitton Cup]].<ref>http://www.cupinfo.com/en/07teampage-main.php</ref><ref>http://www.sailing.org/news/18708.php#.WXALHVFLftQ</ref>\n\nAfter his career in sports have he been producing sails and have widely been used as sailing advisor by teams on all levels as well as single sailors.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Footer Olympic Champions Soling}}\n{{Footer World Champions Soling}}\n{{Footer European Champions Soling}}\n{{Footer West German Championship Winners in Soling}}\n{{Footer Swedish Championship Winners in Soling}}\n{{Footer World Champions Dragon}}\n{{Footer World Champions H-Boat}}\n{{Footer World Champions Open Match Racing}}\n{{Denmark-Olympic-medalist-stub}}\n{{Denmark-yachtracing-bio-stub}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Bank, Jesper}}\n[[Category:1957 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Danish male sailors (sport)]]\n[[Category:Dragon class sailors]]\n[[Category:Olympic sailors of Denmark]]\n[[Category:Olympic gold medalists for Denmark]]\n[[Category:Olympic medalists in sailing]]\n[[Category:Sailors at the 1984 Summer Olympics \u2013 Soling]]\n[[Category:Sailors at the 1988 Summer Olympics \u2013 Soling]]\n[[Category:Sailors at the 1992 Summer Olympics \u2013 Soling]]\n[[Category:Sailors at the 2000 Summer Olympics \u2013 Soling]]\n[[Category:H-boat class sailors]]\n[[Category:Medalists at the 2000 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Medalists at the 1992 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Medalists at the 1988 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Olympic bronze medalists for Denmark]]\n[[Category:2007 America's Cup sailors]]\n[[Category:2003 America's Cup sailors]]\n[[Category:European Champions Soling]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Danish sailor and Olympic champion|bot=PearBOT 5}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2015}}\n{{MedalTableTop}}\n{{MedalSport | Men's [[Sailing (sport)|sailing]]}}\n{{MedalCountry | {{DEN}} }}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[Olympic Games]]}}\n{{MedalGold| [[1992 Summer Olympics|1992 Barcelona]] | [[Sailing at the 1992 Summer Olympics|Soling class]]}}\n{{MedalGold| [[2000 Summer Olympics|2000 Sydney]] | [[Sailing at the 2000 Summer Olympics|Soling class]]}}\n{{MedalBronze| [[1988 Summer Olympics|1988 Seoul]] | [[Sailing at the 1988 Summer Olympics|Soling class]]}}\n{{MedalBottom}}\n\n'''Jesper Bank''' (born 6 April 1957 in [[Fredericia]]) is a [[Denmark|Danish]] [[sailor]] and Olympic champion. \nHe received a bronze medal in the ''[[Soling|Soling Class]]'' at the [[1988 Summer Olympics]] in [[Seoul]].<ref name=db-ol1988-sailing>[https://web.archive.org/web/20061031065851/http://www.databaseolympics.com/games/gamessport.htm?g=22&sp=YAT 1988 Summer Olympics &ndash; Seoul, South Korea &ndash; Sailing] &ndash; ''databaseOlympics.com'' (Retrieved on 23 May 2008)</ref>\n\nHe won a gold medal at the [[1992 Summer Olympics]] in [[Barcelona]],<ref name=db-ol1992-sailing>[https://web.archive.org/web/20060218162535/http://databaseolympics.com/games/gamessport.htm?g=23&sp=YAT 1992 Summer Olympics &ndash; Barcelona, Spain &ndash; Sailing] &ndash; ''databaseOlympics.com'' (Retrieved on 23 May 2008)</ref> and again at the [[2000 Summer Olympics]] in [[Sydney]].<ref name=db-ol2000-sailing>[http://www.databaseolympics.com/games/gamessport.htm?g=25&sp=YAT 2000 Summer Olympics &ndash; Sydney, Australia &ndash; Sailing] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131016101855/http://www.databaseolympics.com/games/gamessport.htm?g=25&sp=YAT |date=16 October 2013 }} &ndash; ''databaseOlympics.com'' (Retrieved on 23 May 2008)</ref>\n\nThis makes Jesper Bank among the most winning regatta and match-race sailors seen.\nBetween 1978 (nationally) relatively 1987 (internationally) and 2000 achieved he to be:\n\n- Twice Olympic champion and additional one time bronze medallist. \n\n- 8 times World Champion and additional 5 times medallist.\n\n- 3 times European Champion and additional 3 times medallist.\n\n- Scandinavian Champion and additional two times bronze medallist.\n\n- 9 times national Danish Champion and additional a single Bronze medal.\n\nThe international and some national results though as skipper in 3-crew boat classes.\n\nHe sailed for [[Victory Challenge]] in the [[2003 Louis Vuitton Cup]] and [[United Internet Team Germany]] in the [[2007 Louis Vuitton Cup]].<ref>http://www.cupinfo.com/en/07teampage-main.php</ref><ref>http://www.sailing.org/news/18708.php#.WXALHVFLftQ</ref>\n\nAfter his career in sports have he been producing sails and have widely been used as sailing advisor by teams on all levels as well as single sailors.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Footer Olympic Champions Soling}}\n{{Footer World Champions Dragon}}\n{{Footer World Champions H-Boat}}\n{{Footer World Champions Open Match Racing}}\n{{Footer World Champions Soling}}\n{{Footer West German Championship Winners in Soling}}\n{{Footer Swedish Championship Winners in Soling}}\n{{Denmark-Olympic-medalist-stub}}\n{{Denmark-yachtracing-bio-stub}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Bank, Jesper}}\n[[Category:1957 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Danish male sailors (sport)]]\n[[Category:Dragon class sailors]]\n[[Category:Olympic sailors of Denmark]]\n[[Category:Olympic gold medalists for Denmark]]\n[[Category:Olympic medalists in sailing]]\n[[Category:Sailors at the 1984 Summer Olympics \u2013 Soling]]\n[[Category:Sailors at the 1988 Summer Olympics \u2013 Soling]]\n[[Category:Sailors at the 1992 